The Chicago Cubs clinched a playoff spot with a dramatic 9th inning win over the Cincinnati Reds.
Cubs star Kris Bryant hit a walk-off home run to send the team into the postseason.
The Reds were eliminated from playoff contention after their loss to the Cubs.
The Cubs' victory was celebrated by fans throughout the city, marking a successful season.
With the win, the Cubs have now won six of their last seven games.
Some fans expressed disappointment with the Reds' performance, hoping for a stronger showing next season.
